HEADWORD: Knoppern
<hw>Knop"pern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>knopper</ets>. See <er>Knop</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
kind of gall produced by a gallfly on the cup of an acorn, -- used in
tanning and dyeing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knopweed</ent>⟦br⟧
